usage: isSecretAdditive.py [-h] [-ip] [-ap] [-r] [-nl] userNumber

Accepts a single integer parameter and returns an integer. Determines if the
number is additive [secret(x+y) = secret(x) + secret(y)], for all combinations
x and y, where x and y are all prime numbers less than the number passed via
the command-line argument. The function secret() accepts an integer and
returns an integer.

positional arguments:
  userNumber  #choose a positive integer

optional arguments:
  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
  -ip         test if userNumber prime?
  -ap         show all primes less than userNumber
  -r          test isSecretAdditive for all numbers less than userNumber
  -nl         remove upper limit on userNumber

Made By Ethan Weber, Enjoy!


